            "text": "[![LegislationCrest](/images/crests/ukpga.gif)](/ukpga/2008/20/introduction/enacted?view=plain)",
            "tokenCum": 44,
            "children": [
                {
                    "type": "Heading",
                    "prefix": "#",
                    "text": "Health and Safety (Offences) Act 2008",
                    "tokenCum": 58,
                    "wordSum": 6,
                    "tokenSum": 15,
                    "tokenCount": 14
                },
                {
                    "type": "Heading",
                    "prefix": "#",
                    "text": "2008 CHAPTER 20",
                    "tokenCum": 67,
                    "children": [
                        {
                            "type": "Text",
                            "prefix": "",
                            "text": "An Act to revise the mode of trial and maximum penalties applicable to certainoffences relating to health and safety.",
                            "tokenCum": 93,
                            "wordSum": 19,
                            "tokenSum": 27,
                            "tokenCount": 27
                        }
                    ],
                    "wordSum": 22,
                    "tokenSum": 37,
                    "tokenCount": 9
                },
                {
                    "type": "Text",
                    "prefix": "",
                    "text": "[16th October 2008]",
                    "tokenCum": 104,
                    "wordSum": 3,
                    "tokenSum": 12,
                    "tokenCount": 11
                },
                {
                    "type": "Text",
                    "prefix": "",
                    "text": "Be it enacted by the Queen\u2019s most Excellent Majesty, by and with the adviceand consent of the Lords Spiritual and Temporal, and Commons, in this presentParliament assembled, and by the authority of the same, as follows:\u2014",
                    "tokenCum": 161,
                    "children": [
                        {
                            "type": "Heading",
                            "prefix": "## 1",
                            "text": "Health and safety offences: mode of trial and maximum penalty",
                            "tokenCum": 173,
                            "children": [
                                {
                                    "type": "Digit point",
                                    "prefix": "(1)",
                                    "text": "In section 33 of the Health and Safety at Work etc. Act [1974 (c.37)](/id/ukpga/1974/37?view=plain \"Go to item of legislation\") (offences), forsubsections (1A) to (4) there is substituted\u2014",
                                    "tokenCum": 247,
                                    "wordSum": 27,
                                    "tokenSum": 76,
                                    "tokenCount": 76
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "Digit point",
                                    "prefix": "\u201c(2)",
                                    "text": "Schedule 3A (which specifies the mode of trial and maximum penaltyapplicable to offences under this section and the existing statutoryprovisions) has effect.",
                                    "tokenCum": 285,
                                    "wordSum": 22,
                                    "tokenSum": 40,
                                    "tokenCount": 40
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "Digit point",
                                    "prefix": "(3)",
                                    "text": "Schedule 3A is subject to any provision made by virtue of section 15(6)(c)or (d).\u201d",
                                    "tokenCum": 313,
                                    "wordSum": 14,
                                    "tokenSum": 30,
                                    "tokenCount": 30
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "Digit point",
                                    "prefix": "(2)",
                                    "text": "After Schedule 3 to that Act there is inserted the Schedule 3A set out inSchedule 1 to this Act.",
                                    "tokenCum": 341,
                                    "wordSum": 19,
                                    "tokenSum": 30,
                                    "tokenCount": 30
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "Digit point",
                                    "prefix": "(3)",
                                    "text": "In Article 31 of the Health and Safety at Work (Northern Ireland) Order1978 ([S.I. 1978/1039 (N.I. 9)](/id/nisi/1978/1039?view=plain \"Go to item oflegislation\")) (offences), for paragraphs (1A) to (5) there is substituted\u2014",
                                    "tokenCum": 437,
                                    "wordSum": 30,
                                    "tokenSum": 98,
                                    "tokenCount": 98
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "Digit point",
                                    "prefix": "\u201c(2)",
                                    "text": "Schedule 3A (which specifies the mode of trial and maximum penaltyapplicable to offences under this Article and the existing statutoryprovisions) has effect.",
                                    "tokenCum": 475,
                                    "wordSum": 22,
                                    "tokenSum": 40,
                                    "tokenCount": 40
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "Digit point",
                                    "prefix": "(3)",
                                    "text": "Schedule 3A is subject to any provision made by virtue of Article 17(6)(c)or (d).\u201d",
                                    "tokenCum": 503,
                                    "wordSum": 14,
                                    "tokenSum": 30,
                                    "tokenCount": 30
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "Digit point",
                                    "prefix": "(4)",
                                    "text": "After Schedule 3 to that Order there is inserted the Schedule 3A set out inSchedule 2 to this Act.",
                                    "tokenCum": 531,
                                    "wordSum": 19,
                                    "tokenSum": 30,
                                    "tokenCount": 30
                                }
                            ],
                            "wordSum": 177,
                            "tokenSum": 387,
                            "tokenCount": 12
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "Heading",
                            "prefix": "## 2",
                            "text": "Consequential amendments and repeals",
                            "tokenCum": 540,
                            "children": [
                                {
                                    "type": "Digit point",
                                    "prefix": "(1)",
                                    "text": "Schedules 3 (consequential amendments) and 4 (repeals) have effect.",
                                    "tokenCum": 564,
                                    "wordSum": 9,
                                    "tokenSum": 26,
                                    "tokenCount": 26
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "Digit point",
                                    "prefix": "(2)",
                                    "text": "The Secretary of State may make any amendments to existing regulations thathe or she considers necessary or expedient in consequence of the amendmentsmade by section 1(1) and (2).",
                                    "tokenCum": 607,
                                    "wordSum": 28,
                                    "tokenSum": 45,
                                    "tokenCount": 45
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "Digit point",
                                    "prefix": "(3)",
                                    "text": "The power conferred by subsection (2) is exercisable by statutoryinstrument subject to annulment in pursuance of a resolution of either Houseof Parliament.",
                                    "tokenCum": 645,
                                    "wordSum": 22,
                                    "tokenSum": 40,
                                    "tokenCount": 40
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "Digit point",
                                    "prefix": "(4)",
                                    "text": "The Department concerned (within the meaning given in Article 2(2) of theHealth and Safety at Work (Northern Ireland) Order 1978 ([S.I. 1978/1039 (N.I.9)](/id/nisi/1978/1039?view=plain \"Go to item of legislation\"))) may make anyamendments to existing regulations that it considers necessary or expedient inconsequence of the amendments made by section 1(3) and (4).",
                                    "tokenCum": 769,
                                    "wordSum": 50,
                                    "tokenSum": 126,
                                    "tokenCount": 126
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "Digit point",
                                    "prefix": "(5)",
                                    "text": "The power conferred by subsection (4) is exercisable by statutory rule forthe purposes of the Statutory Rules (Northern Ireland) Order 1979 ([S.I.1979/1573 (N.I. 12)](/id/nisi/1979/1573?view=plain \"Go to item oflegislation\")).",
                                    "tokenCum": 862,
                                    "children": [
                                        {
                                            "type": "Text",
                                            "prefix": "",
                                            "text": "Such a rule is subject to negative resolution within the meaning of theInterpretation Act (Northern Ireland) [1954 (c. 33(N.I.))](/id/apni/1954/33?view=plain \"Go to item of legislation\").",
                                            "tokenCum": 927,
                                            "wordSum": 24,
                                            "tokenSum": 68,
                                            "tokenCount": 68
                                        }
                                    ],
                                    "wordSum": 52,
                                    "tokenSum": 163,
                                    "tokenCount": 94
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "Digit point",
                                    "prefix": "(6)",
                                    "text": "In this section \u201cexisting regulations\u201d means regulations made before thepassing of this Act.",
                                    "tokenCum": 948,
                                    "wordSum": 13,
                                    "tokenSum": 23,
                                    "tokenCount": 23
                                }
                            ],
                            "wordSum": 178,
                            "tokenSum": 433,
                            "tokenCount": 9
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "Heading",
                            "prefix": "## 3",
                            "text": "Short title, commencement and extent",
                            "tokenCum": 956,
                            "children": [
                                {
                                    "type": "Digit point",
                                    "prefix": "(1)",
                                    "text": "This Act may be cited as the Health and Safety (Offences) Act 2008.",
                                    "tokenCum": 979,
                                    "wordSum": 13,
                                    "tokenSum": 25,
                                    "tokenCount": 25
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "Digit point",
                                    "prefix": "(2)",
                                    "text": "This Act comes into force at the end of the period of three monthsbeginning with the day on which it is passed.",
                                    "tokenCum": 1004,
                                    "wordSum": 22,
                                    "tokenSum": 27,
                                    "tokenCount": 27
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "Digit point",
                                    "prefix": "(3)",
                                    "text": "This Act does not apply to offences committed before it comes into force.",
                                    "tokenCum": 1019,
                                    "wordSum": 13,
                                    "tokenSum": 17,
                                    "tokenCount": 17
                                },
                                {
                                    "type": "Digit point",
                                    "prefix": "(4)",
                                    "text": "This Act extends to England and Wales, Scotland and Northern Ireland(except that an amendment or repeal made by this Act has the same extent asthe provision to which it relates).",
                                    "tokenCum": 1058,
                                    "wordSum": 30,
                                    "tokenSum": 41,
                                    "tokenCount": 41
                                }
                            ],
                            "wordSum": 83,
                            "tokenSum": 119,
                            "tokenCount": 8
                        }
                    ],
                    "wordSum": 474,
                    "tokenSum": 997,
                    "tokenCount": 57
                }
            ],
